WEBVTT

00:01.735 --> 00:05.500
very much surprised at how peaceful things seemed 
to be. It had no sense of impending doom or

00:05.741 --> 00:09.726
anything. Can you carry us from that point till you 
got back to your hotel? One of the things that I was

00:15.395 --> 00:23.026
thinking was I wish that our whole family was there 
so that they could see what's going on. There's no

00:23.346 --> 00:31.658
way, I knew there was no way I could explain how 
peaceful and how cooperative these people were

00:23.346 --> 00:31.658
because many times when we were over here, Very 
seldom do we see people helping each other out,

00:32.110 --> 00:38.841
people united in a common cause, a common idea. And 
even when you would try to get on a Chinese bus, it

00:38.881 --> 00:44.149
was survival of the fittest. And they would run 
over you to get onto the bus. But here, you had more

00:47.374 --> 00:53.664
people in a potentially dangerous situation, but 
they were very calm. They were very helpful to each

00:54.225 --> 00:59.974
other. It just, it was something that we had never 
experienced. You're comparing the crowd in June

01:04.426 --> 01:17.861
of 1989 as peaceful and calm compared to the daily 
activity, crowds, and movement in Beijing back in

01:04.426 --> 01:17.861
your 85, 86 school year. Yes, yes. I said there were 
more people, and I said there were just, you could

01:19.663 --> 01:30.636
see that these people, although I could not 
understand what they were saying, that they were

01:19.663 --> 01:30.636
pleading with these troops not to go into 
Tiananmen Square. You felt that's what they were

01:33.615 --> 01:35.657
doing? Oh, yeah. There was no doubt in my mind. They 
were trying to tell these troops that these were

01:38.259 --> 01:57.136
people down in Tiananmen Square, students and 
otherwise, and that they were not ruffians or

01:38.259 --> 01:57.136
hooligans that were causing destruction or 
anything like that, and trying to explain the

01:38.259 --> 01:57.136
general situation and what was going on. It was a 
very... friendly type of thing. The soldiers were

02:01.812 --> 02:28.855
doing more listening than talking, and they had a 
rather solemn look on their face for the most part,

02:01.812 --> 02:28.855
but it was not what it could have been and what I 
could have imagined as a confrontational type of

02:01.812 --> 02:28.855
situation, even though there were, I would guess 
here at this intersection by this time, there were

02:01.812 --> 02:28.855
maybe 5,000 to 10,000 people, because they 
literally covered This whole interchange there

02:29.290 --> 02:33.135
was thick with people.

02:36.779 --> 02:41.525
But I said it was a very peaceful atmosphere. And 
people did not seem to be afraid. I mean, when

02:44.128 --> 02:45.951
somebody's afraid, you can see it in their eyes. 
You can see it in the way they were acting. And these

02:47.573 --> 02:49.775
people were not acting that way. It was a very 
friendly type of thing. And the Chinese people,

02:54.061 --> 02:55.983
they love their children. They're not going to put 
their children what they would feel is a

02:58.906 --> 03:02.030
potentially dangerous situation. Yet there were 
children all over. They were playing on the grass

03:04.333 --> 03:13.526
nearby, and walking around, and children talking 
with troops too. So it was a very peaceful setting.

03:18.213 --> 03:25.082
So you were still walking, still heading for the 
taxi? So about 9.30, I figured, well, you know, I

03:25.349 --> 03:30.273
better go ahead and get back again. Nothing out of 
the ordinary seemed to be happening. So I walked on

03:34.397 --> 03:36.979
to the Friendship store. It was closed by this 
time, so there weren't any taxis there, so I had to

03:37.580 --> 03:44.125
go down to one of the foreign hotels that's a little 
bit further on. And there were a couple of taxis

03:45.046 --> 03:55.035
there, but they weren't too enthused about taking 
someone somewhere, so I had to bargain with this

03:55.454 --> 03:56.575
guy. He wanted 50 or 60 yuan to take me what is 
