I put that I could carry very easily. I put some of 
the food in there and some of the things that I felt

25:07.746 --> 25:17.655
were more necessities in my bigger, hard-sided 
bag. I put things that I could do without if I had to

25:18.155 --> 25:23.079
ditch that. And I

25:23.900 --> 25:36.030
went to the desk and changed some of my money into

25:36.837 --> 25:38.358
dollars, got some dollars. You have to convert 
into foreign exchange. I got some of that. I had

25:42.823 --> 25:49.109
some Chinese local currency, and I also had some 
dollars. And I spread those around on my body and in

25:49.129 --> 25:59.819
my different bags so that if I was separated from 
one of them, I wouldn't have all my eggs in one

25:49.129 --> 25:59.819
basket, so to speak. And I brought along a Swiss 
Army knife because that's helpful in the as we

26:06.301 --> 26:10.825
found out before, and fortunately had that with 
me, so I put that in my pocket. And then went down and

26:11.766 --> 26:34.148
waited for a cab, and fortunately, about half an 
hour after I got out there, somebody was coming to,

26:11.766 --> 26:34.148
because tourists, American tourists, were still 
arriving Monday afternoon, and I talked back and

26:11.766 --> 26:34.148
had to bargain with this guy again, but got him to 
take me out to the airport, I was somewhat

26:35.208 --> 26:39.212
concerned because normally there's just a taxi 
driver. But in this cab, there was a taxi driver.

26:42.115 --> 26:45.919
There was a friend of his also sitting in the front 
seat. And I was concerned that these guys might try

26:45.939 --> 26:56.609
to rob me or they might take me out somewhere and 
leave me off there. But it was the only cab that had

26:57.110 --> 26:59.032
come around. So I figured I'd go ahead and take a 
chance. And so I got in the back seat. I let him put

27:06.494 --> 27:13.403
the heavy bag in the trunk, but I kept the other kind 
of carry-on bag type thing with me. And I had my

27:14.304 --> 27:16.668
pocket knife. That would have done me, I don't 
know, but easily accessible to me. And we got into

27:22.395 --> 27:25.199
the cab and we started going out there. And the 
driver knew a little bit of English and started a

27:26.100 --> 27:33.090
little bit of a conversation. And he had... a copy 
of a fax that they had received earlier in the day

27:36.380 --> 27:43.687
from Hong Kong. What the students and the people in 
Beijing were doing was they were getting most of

27:43.908 --> 27:52.036
their information from outside China, from Hong 
Kong. And what they would do was in Hong Kong, they

27:52.056 --> 28:01.526
would watch what was going on from the news and from 
their contacts, the people that they knew, and

27:52.056 --> 28:01.526
then they would write it out in Chinese 
characters. Then they would fax it to Beijing, and

28:01.546 --> 28:04.969
then people are sympathetic to the 
demonstrations. They would take them, and they

28:07.755 --> 28:12.460
would run off copies, which is very difficult to 
get access to a copy machine in China. It's not like

28:12.480 --> 28:17.044
here, where you just run down to Kiko's or 
someplace, four cents a copy place. And they would

28:17.985 --> 28:23.910
make copies, and then they would, as I mentioned, 
the students were distributing these, putting

28:17.985 --> 28:23.910
them on light poles and stuff like that. But this 
guy had a stack of them, and he gave me one of them,

28:24.531 --> 28:30.716
which I've had translated since I came back. And it 
was dealing with the massacre that's going on

28:35.020 --> 28:36.262
Saturday night, Sunday morning. It was square, 
what was going on, Tiananmen Square. And as we were

28:40.648 --> 28:49.400
going, I knew, again, because I'd been there, I 
knew the general streets and the general

28:40.648 --> 28:49.400
directions. So I was watching very carefully as to 
where these guys were taking me, so that I could

28:49.420 --> 28:54.428
tell if they were taking me or not. But they were 
going the route that you would go to get out there.

29:00.176 --> 29:04.622
And on two occasions, we passed a major 
intersection where there were several trucks of

29:05.041 --> 29:08.685
troops over on the side. And they were armed, but 
they weren't out there blocking off the street or

29:09.586 --> 29:13.770
that. They were just kind of camped over to the 
side. Well, the second group that we came up to was

29:19.356 --> 29:32.230
at the intersection of the road that goes out to the 
airport.

29:33.644 --> 29:59.517
lido the holiday inn is located right there on that 
intersection there were about four trucks they

29:33.644 --> 29:59.517
were there the troops they were out they were they 
were eating and mulling around and the driver as we

29:33.644 --> 29:59.517
started to go on this intersection he started 
rolling down his window and grabbed one of these

29:33.644 --> 29:59.517
faxes to give these soldiers and i thought you know 
this guy is going to get us killed right here and I

30:00.323 --> 30:09.472
was glad that his friend was in the front seat with 
him because his friend kind of, you know, nudged

30:00.323 --> 30:09.472
him on the arm and, you know, shook his head, you 
know, don't do this. And so he turned all over on the

30:10.113 --> 30:19.222
seat next to us so that even somebody looking in 
couldn't see him and rolled the window back up and

30:10.113 --> 30:19.222
we drove on. And it was great news with that. We got 
out to the airport. It was about 4 o'clock in the

30:26.189 --> 30:29.132
afternoon. And one time I see the

30:30.479 --> 30:39.657
United Airlines flight that my kids were supposed 
to come in. It was supposed to get into Beijing

30:39.677 --> 30:42.181
Monday night. And what it does is it's coming and 
going.

